PN,31503
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1775837470
OL,3,CKey moments in the Artemis II mission
OL,4,Cso far
OL,6,FThe Artemis II crew lost all
OL,7,Fcommunications with Earth for around
OL,8,F40 minutes when Orion moved behind the
OL,9,Fmoon, as it blocked the radio signals
OL,10,Fneeded for the Deep Space Network to
OL,11,Fconnect to the spacecraft.
OL,13,FThe blackout was expected and the
OL,14,Fastronauts did a lot of training for
OL,15,Fit ahead of time.
OL,17,FDuring the blackout the Orion made its
OL,18,Fclosest approach to the moon and
OL,19,Freached its maximum distance from
OL,20,FEarth.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
