PN,31504
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1775837470
OL,3,CKey moments in the Artemis II mission
OL,4,Cso far
OL,6,F"We will see you on the other side,"
OL,7,Fpilot Victor Glover said a couple of
OL,8,Fminutes before the connection was lost.
OL,10,FThe furthest away mankind has ever been
OL,12,FOn its journey around the moon, the
OL,13,FOrion spacecraft reached its maximum
OL,14,Fdistance from Earth, thought to be
OL,15,Faround 252,756 miles.
OL,17,FIt is a new record, beating the
OL,18,Festimated 248,655 miles travelled by
OL,19,FApollo 13 in 1970, meaning the Artemis
OL,20,FII crew has travelled further from
OL,21,FEarth than any other human beings.
OL,26,@nD@AOUnD@dO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/12
