PN,31506
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1775837470
OL,3,CKey moments in the Artemis II mission
OL,4,Cso far
OL,6,FWhile the astronauts did not touch
OL,7,Fdown on the moon, the mission paves
OL,8,Fthe way for a future lunar landing and
OL,9,Falso lays the foundation to send a
OL,10,Fcrew to Mars.
OL,12,FTotal solar eclipse
OL,14,FDuring the lunar flyby the crew also
OL,15,Fwitnessed a 53-minute solar eclipse.
OL,17,FThe sun appeared to pass behind the
OL,18,Fmoon while the Orion was on its far
OL,19,Fside.
OL,21,FNaming a crater
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31507
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1775837470
OL,3,CKey moments in the Artemis II mission
OL,4,Cso far
OL,6,FOn Monday the astronauts asked to name
OL,7,Ftwo craters on the moon - one
OL,8,FIntegrity, after their spacecraft, and
OL,9,Fthe second Carroll, after Commander
OL,10,FReid Wiseman's late wife, who died of
OL,11,Fcancer in 2020.
OL,13,F"There's a feature in a really neat
OL,14,Fplace on the moon, and it is on the
OL,15,Fnear-side, far-side boundary... It's
OL,16,Fjust on the near side of that
OL,17,Fboundary, so at certain times in the
OL,18,Fmoon's transit around Earth we will be
OL,19,Fable to see this from Earth," mission
OL,20,Fspecialist Jeremy Hansen said.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31508
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1775837470
OL,3,CKey moments in the Artemis II mission
OL,4,Cso far
OL,6,F"We lost a loved one, her name was
OL,7,FCarroll, the spouse of Reid, the
OL,8,Fmother of Katie and Ellie ... It's a
OL,9,Fbright spot on the moon."
OL,11,FThe astronauts were visibly emotional
OL,12,Fas they put in the name request, which
OL,13,Fwill be sent to the International
OL,14,FAstronomical Union for approval.
OL,16,FThere are more than 9,000 officially
OL,17,Fnamed features on the moon, many of
OL,18,Fwhich are craters. The would-be
OL,19,FCarroll crater is just to the north
OL,20,Fwest of Glushko, at the same latitude
OL,21,Fas Ohm.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
