PN,31509
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1775837470
OL,3,CKey moments in the Artemis II mission
OL,4,Cso far
OL,6,FToilet troubles
OL,8,FShortly after launch last week, the
OL,9,FArtemis II crew realised the toilet
OL,10,Fpump wasn't working.
OL,12,FThe problem was quickly resolved
OL,13,Fthough when they realised they hadn't
OL,14,Fadded enough water to prime the pump
OL,15,Fand the system started to work as
OL,16,Fplanned.
OL,18,FBut that wasn't the only issue. Three
OL,19,Fdays into the mission, the Orion
OL,20,Fcapsule experienced more issues with
OL,21,Fits waste management.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31510
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1775837470
OL,3,CKey moments in the Artemis II mission
OL,4,Cso far
OL,6,F"It's an issue with dumping the waste
OL,7,Fout of the toilet," Artemis II Flight
OL,8,FDirector Judd Frieling told reporters
OL,9,Fon Saturday morning. "And so it
OL,10,Fappears to me that we probably have
OL,11,Fsome frozen urine in the vent line."
OL,13,FMission control continued to
OL,14,Ftroubleshoot the issue as the
OL,15,Fastronauts slept and managed to warm
OL,16,Fup the frozen line by rotating the
OL,17,Fcapsule to put the frozen urine into
OL,18,Fthe sun.
OL,26,@nD@AOUoD@SO]qD@VOUsD@dO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
